title: Excellent phosphorus-doped porous carbon oxygen reduction reaction catalysts derived from natural wild Angelica dahurica
content:
RSC Sustain., 2024, Advance Article
DOI: 10.1039/D4SU00182F, Paper
Open Access

Wenhao Mo, Xiaohua Tan, Lei Zhao
WAD directly carbonized at 900 °C has a half-wave potential of 0.822 V relative to a reversible hydrogen electrode, a limiting current density of 4.54 mA cm−2 at 1600 rpm, an average number of transferred electrons of four, and a stability of 95.9% for 20 000 s, larger than the 82.6% of Pt/C.
